itemDescription: Marks, Geoffrey (1864–1938), actuary and insurance company manager

wikipedia_page.main: Geoffrey Marks (15 November 1864 – 25 August 1938) was an English first-class cricketer active 1894–1900 who played for Middlesex. He was born in Thornton Heath, Surrey; died in Newnham, Hampshire.

response: Geoffrey Marks (2 January 1932 – 30 August 1990) was a Sri Lankan swimmer. He competed in three events at the 1952 Summer Olympics.
